<HEADLINE>
<P>
DOWNTIME: BODY WATCH; COMMUNING WITH A ROOSTER IN THE EARLY HOURS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 No matter what time I go to bed, I still am a very early riser.I have learned 
to deal with it by walking across the street to my neighbor's yard to visit her 
rooster. He has black-and-gray feathers and is quite magnificent in height. As 
he begins to crow, I advance toward him, offering his first meal of the day. I 
enjoy this early time as I have befriended the rooster; believe it or not, I 
now do a pretty good cock-a-doodle-doo myself. 
</P>
<P>
 -- PEARL KELL, Murrieta 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
