<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; USC; MISSED BLOCKS PUT WALTERS IN DOGHOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 USC tailback Shawn Walters is in the doghouse, but might be released after 
only a day or two. 
</P>
<P>
 Walters missed two blocks that resulted in two of UCLA's six sacks of Rob 
Johnson in the loss on Saturday.Walters, who has a cracked thumb, started 
against UCLA but had only three carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Backup Leonard Green gained 86 yards in 18 carries and scored a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Coach John Robinson said Walters would be the starter against Notre Dame. The 
225-pound sophomore is averaging five yards per carry and has gained 852 yards 
this season. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Saturday's 5 p.m. Coliseum game against the Irish is sold out. . . . USC wide 
receiver Keyshawn Johnson went over 1,000 yards for the season against UCLA, 
with 11 receptions for 175 yards. He is only the third Trojan to go over 1,000 
in receiving yardage, joining Johnnie Morton, 1,520 in in 1993, and Gary 
Wellman, 1,015, in 1990. . . . Notre Dame's sophomore quarterback, Ron Powlus, 
needs one touchdown pass against USC to become Notre Dame's all-time 
single-season record holder with 19. . . . Both USC and its opponents are 
converting 35.4% of their third downs. . . . USC defensive coordinator Don 
Lindsey and safeties coach Keith Burns are former assistants under Notre Dame 
Coach Lou Holtz, when he was at Arkansas. . . . Notre Dame leads in the USC 
series, 38-23-4, and has won the last 11, longest streak in the series, which 
began in 1926. Before that, USC had won five in a row, 1978-82. John Robinson's 
five-game winning streak over Notre Dame ended at South Bend last season, in a 
31-13 Irish victory. EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
