<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL 1994-1995 / GOLDEN WEST LEAGUE; OCEAN VIEW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 1993-94 RECORDS OVERALL: 14-14 LEAGUE: 8-6 
</P>
<P>
 COACH: RECORD AT SCHOOL Jim Harris: 287-131 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS 
YR. HGT. P Dan McDonald Sr. 6-1 F 04,15,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Ali 
Enriquez Sr. 6-0 G Matt Hanson Sr. 6-6 C 04,15,05,06,05 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. 
P Matt Clark Sr. 6-0 G David Hatch Fr. 6-2 F Matt Kiemle Fr. 6-3 F Jason 
Martini Fr. 6-3 G Aaron Mullen Jr. 6-0 G/F Viet Nguyen Sr. 5-5 G Eric Petersen 
Jr. 6-5 F/C Mike Seguin Jr. 6-0 G David Wilson Sr. 6-6 F/C OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 The Seahawks did some damage after earning an at-large bid to the Southern 
Section Division II-AA playoffs, winning their first-round game, 55-53, in 
overtime against El Monte Mountain View. They pushed fourth-seeded Glendora 
before losing, 58-53. Harris is confident that a return trip to the playoffs is 
probable with this squad. McDonald averaged 10 points in his first varsity 
season and might double that figure. Like many Seahawks, McDonald is an 
aggressive defender and good shooter. Harris has the luxury of depth and size, 
a combination many of his league colleagues wish their teams had. Hanson has a 
nice touch near the basket and should provide a solid defensive presence at 
center. Enriquez can dribble, score and pass -- skills most coaches hope their 
guards possess. Petersen and Wilson provide excellent front-court 
possibilities. 
</P>
