<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Northridge safety Joe Vaughn, a senior from Sylmar, has been named 
American West Conference Defensive Player of the Year. Vaughn tied a school 
record with nine interceptions this year and broke the NCAA Division I-AA 
record for interception return yardage. 
</P>
<P>
 Matador quarterback J.J. O'Laughlin, receiver Duc Ngo, offensive lineman Edvin 
Babayova and kicker Matt Ornelaz also made the first-team offense. Defensive 
lineman Oscar Wilson and defensive back Vincent Johnson made the first-team 
defense. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Nordhoff High girls' tennis team might consider throwing in its rackets 
right now, because recent history suggests the Rangers will have little chance 
in their Southern Section Division V team championship match. 
</P>
<P>
 But if the third time really is a charm, Nordhoff (14-6) could upset 
fourth-seeded La Reina (15-3) in the 2 p.m. showdown today at the Ojai Valley 
Racquet Club. 
</P>
<P>
 "They wiped us off the court," Nordhoff Coach Rose Boggs said. "Now it depends 
on what the girls want to do. They've improved. It's just how they perform 
under pressure." 
</P>
<P>
 For La Reina, sisters Kristy Bear (30-2), a sophomore, and Cindy Bear (25-7), 
a senior, alternate at Nos. 1 and 2 singles. Kristin Dickey is 30-3 at No. 3 
singles. The No. 1 doubles team of Katie Nelson and Vicki Hull (66-0) have not 
lost a match in two seasons. DANA HADDAD 
</P>
