<HEADLINE>
<P>
FREEDOM BOWL SIGNS NEW SPONSOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE DiGIOVANNA, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Freedom Bowl received some financial relief Monday with the addition of 
Bank of America as a presenting sponsor, signing a two-year deal that will pump 
"in excess of six figures," into the postseason college football game in 
Anaheim Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 With expenses rising -- the NCAA increased its minimum bowl-game payout from 
$500,000 per team in 1991 to $750,000 this year -- and gate receipts 
fluctuating from year to year, the Freedom Bowl's budget deficit has risen to 
about $1 million. 
</P>
<P>
 But the presenting sponsorship should enable the Freedom Bowl to at least 
cover annual expenses and prevent the deficit from growing, according to Don 
Andersen, executive director of the Orange County Sports Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 "With ticket sales from the two conferences (Pacific 10 and Western Athletic), 
the television contract (with Raycom) and the Bank of America deal, it 
guarantees that we're going to cover all our payments," Andersen said. "There's 
a certain comfort in that, obviously." 
</P>
<P>
 Andersen said the Freedom Bowl, which will be played for the 11th time Dec. 
27, was not in danger of being discontinued like the Pigskin Classic, the 
preseason game that recently lost its title sponsorship from Disneyland and 
will not return to Anaheim Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 "But this keeps us out of that range," said Andersen, who is still seeking a 
title sponsor for the Freedom Bowl. "Down the line we could have gotten into 
that position. This puts us over the hump. It's a real step forward for the 
game." 
</P>
<P>
 This year's Freedom Bowl will feature Utah (9-2) against either Arizona or 
Washington State. The outcomes of Arizona's game against Arizona State Friday 
night in Tucson and the USC-Notre Dame game Saturday in Los Angeles will 
determine the the Utes' opponent. 
</P>
<P>
 The Utes, No. 13 in the CNN-USA Today coaches poll, are the highest ranked 
team to play in the game, and their record equals the previous Freedom 
Bowl-best of Tulsa, which was 9-2 entering the 1991 game against San Diego 
State. 
</P>
</TEXT>
