Made."The show centered on two urban bachelor roommates with an attractive maid 
and suspicious girlfriends, and aired in 1983-84. Despite failing health, 
Villard made several appearances in the past year on episodes of "Frasier," 
"Sisters" and "Star Trek: Deep Space 9." He had earlier appeared in "Hunter," 
"Who's the Boss?" "Golden Girls" and "Taxi." Villard's film credits included 
"Heartbreak Ridge," "My Girl" and the title role in "The Trouble With Dick," 
which won a grand prize at the Sundance Film Festival. On Nov. 14 in Los 
Angeles of complications of AIDS. 
</P>
</TEXT>
