<TEXT>
<P>
 Unless there's an explosion in the local economy, Garden Grove's job market 
isn't expected to grow very much in the next 25 years, according to a county 
report. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials expect about 80 new jobs to be created yearly in the city. 
</P>
<P>
 The county projects that Garden Grove will have 48,000 jobs in 1995. By 2020, 
the city should have about 50,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Mirroring a statewide trend, most of these new jobs will be in the service 
industry, such as in lodging and food service, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove has population of 150,000. Today 
</P>
<P>
 Youngsters will celebrate the autumn 
</P>
<P>
 season at an "Apples, Acorns and Leaves" workshop. 
</P>
<P>
 The city of Los Alamitos is presenting the event, which will run from 1 to 
2:30 p.m. at the Los Alamitos Recreation and Community Services Department, 
10911 Oak St. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshop, for 3- to 6-year-olds, will feature stories, crafts, games and 
refreshments. 
</P>
<P>
 The fee is $12. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (310) 430-1073. 
