<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: SUN VALLEY; PARENT GRADUATES TO TELL PERSONAL STORIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM MAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Graduates of Hope In Youth's parenting empowerment class will be honored at a 
7 p.m. ceremony today at Holy Rosary Church, 7800 Vineland Ave., Sun Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 The ceremony will feature the personal stories of three of the 18 graduating 
parents who will describe their experiences and the ways Hope In Youth helped 
them. 
</P>
<P>
 Hope In Youth is a Los Angeles-based gang prevention program geared toward 
at-risk youths and their parents. Some of the programs are designed by the 
young people themselves. The organization, which is about a year old, is an 
outgrowth of several Catholic charities linked with other charitable 
organizations and religious denominations. 
</P>
<P>
 The organization's parenting classes are designed to improve communication 
skills, encourage parents to take more active roles in the children's lives and 
boost self-confidence. The goal is to ultimately make schools and neighborhoods 
safer by developing stronger family relationships and teaching parents and 
children how to participate in government and community affairs. 
</P>
<P>
 About 2,100 parents have graduated from the 12-week program in the Los Angeles 
area. 
</P>
<P>
 For further information about Hope In Youth programs in the Sun Valley area, 
contact Maria Cabral at (818) 765-1683. TIM MAY 
</P>
</TEXT>
