<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; SANTA CLARITA MAN SUSPECT IN RAPE, CHILD 
MOLESTATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 40-year-old Santa Clarita man was arrested early Monday for allegedly 
molesting a young girl and then raping a San Fernando Valley prostitute, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Steven Bloomer was arrested on suspicion of rape and kidnap after a prostitute 
told police that he picked her up and took her to a Santa Clarita location 
where she saw him molest a girl, about 5 years old, said Detective Bill Looney 
of the sheriff's child abuse detail. 
</P>
<P>
 The prostitute told police that after he molested the young girl, Bloomer 
forced the prostitute to perform various sexual acts on him and then raped her, 
Looney said. The prostitute, whose name was not disclosed, was apparently kept 
at the location for several hours before she escaped. 
</P>
<P>
 The little girl has been placed into protective custody, Looney said. 
</P>
