<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; PAINTED TILES WILL SHOW SUPPORT FOR ZOO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Supporters of the Santa Ana Zoo are being asked to help "Pave the Way" for 
improvements at the new Rain Forest Conservation Exhibit by painting 
animal-related designs on tiles that will be permanently displayed near the 
exhibit. 
</P>
<P>
 The zoo will supply the 12-by-12-inch blank tiles, paints and kiln firing for 
a $100 contribution.Proceeds will pay for seating and educational displays 
adjacent to the ecology-themed exhibit. 
</P>
<P>
 Leading the fund-raising effort is the Friends of Santa Ana Zoo. The support 
group conducted a similar tile-painting project last year to help pay for the 
Amazon's Edge exhibit of South American animals. 
</P>
<P>
 The zoo, at 1801 E. Chestnut Ave. in Santa Ana's Prentice Park, is open from 
10 a.m. to 4 p.m. daily. 
</P>
<P>
 Additional information is available from the Friends of Santa Ana Zoo at (714) 
953-8555. ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
