<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SADDLEBACK / SOUTH BEACH; MISSION VIEJO; COLLEGE TO OFFER 
CLASSES AT SOME HIGH SCHOOLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saddleback College is offering courses this spring for high school students in 
the Capistrano Unified and Saddleback Unified school districts. 
</P>
<P>
 The courses give high school students a chance to get an early start on a 
college education by earning transferable units.Courses include applied 
psychology, business, English, Japanese and sign language. 
</P>
<P>
 The deadline to register is Nov. 30. 
</P>
<P>
 The classes will take place in the late afternoon and early evening at 
different campuses in both school districts. Five classes are being offered at 
each school district. 
</P>
<P>
 The cost for each class is $13 per unit, plus the price of any textbooks and 
materials. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the Saddleback Valley Unified School District at 
(714) 580-3222, or Saddleback College at (714) 582-4555. 
</P>
