<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: NEWPORT / COSTA MESA / IRVINE; NEWPORT BEACH; PARENTS, 
PUPILS SOUGHT FOR DRESS CODE PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Newport-Mesa Unified School District is seeking five parents and five 
students from within the district to serve on a Uniform/Dress Code Task Force. 
</P>
<P>
 The task force, led by elementary and secondary education directors Susan 
Despenas and Tom Jacobsen, will consider dress-related problems in the district 
and form guidelines and a procedure for each school to set its own dress 
code.The panel will also include three administrators, four teachers, one 
classified employee and Community Communications Director Nadine Wilck. 
</P>
<P>
 Duties will include reviewing plans at other schools that have set up uniform 
policies; gathering information from the community about their preferences for 
dress codes; developing districtwide guidelines, and recommending them to the 
school board for adoption. 
</P>
<P>
 The panel is expected to meet four or five times before making recommendations 
to the board in March. 
</P>
<P>
 Applicants should submit a letter of interest to Jacobsen at 1601 16th St., 
Newport Beach, 92663. Letters must be postmarked by Wednesday. HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
