<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: NEW WORLD NAMES INTERNATIONAL TV CHIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Armando Nunez Jr. has been named president of New World International 
Television Distribution. James M. McNamara, president and chief executive of 
New World Entertainment, says Nunez was appointed to the newly created position 
to tap into the vast potential of international sales and co-productions. 
</P>
<P>
 Nunez formerly worked as executive vice president of international sales at 
Viacom Entertainment/Paramount Television Group. New World Entertainment is a 
subsidiary of New World Communications Group. 
</P>
<P>
 * David Sameth has signed an exclusive production agreement with Universal 
Pictures. He will leave his job as a Universal production executive to form the 
company. Sameth joined Universal in 1987 as vice president of creative 
advertising. 
</P>
<P>
 * Robert E. Barron has been named senior vice president of finance for 
Twentieth Television's network TV division. Twentieth Television is a unit of 
20th Century Fox. Barron formerly worked as vice president of international 
finance at Sony Pictures Entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
 * John C. Reece is the new vice president of information technology for Time 
Warner Inc. He was formerly an executive with insurance company Alexander & 
Alexander. 
</P>
<P>
 * Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer has named William A. Jones executive vice president for 
corporate affairs. Jones came to MGM in 1983 and served as general counsel for 
11 years. 
</P>
<P>
 * David Brenner has been named senior vice president of sales and marketing 
for advertiser-supported programming at MCA Television and Home Entertainment 
Groups. 
</P>
<P>
 * Colette Sartor and George Cheeks have joined the law firm of Sinclair 
Tenenbaum & Olesiuk as entertainment associates. 
</P>
<P>
 * Bob Cahill is the new senior vice president of field marketing at EMI 
Records. 
</P>
<P>
 * Cynthia Lieberman has been named vice president of television marketing for 
Samuel Goldwyn Co. She was formerly executive director of Warner Bros. domestic 
television distribution. The company has also hired Ilyse B. Horowitz as 
director of creative advertising. 
</P>
<P>
 * Elizabeth Rezler has been named director of the music division at Warren 
Cowan & Associates. She is the founder and former president of Midtown Press 
Records. 
</P>
<P>
 * Ed Solorzano is the new vice president of development for Patchett Kaufmann 
Entertainment. 
