<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: MTI TO SELL MAGNETIC TAPE STORAGE SYSTEMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 MTI Technology Corp. said Monday that it has formed a joint venture with 
Breece Hill Technologies Inc. of Boulder, Colo., to develop, sell and support a 
family of systems to store data on magnetic tape. MTI said it will invest 
$250,000 in cash for a 3.5% stake in Breece Hill and will market that company's 
products under the MTI label. The Anaheim-based MTI designs, manufactures and 
sells data storage products for several types of office computer networks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA112294-0222 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 101164 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
November 22, 1994, Tuesday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
