<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: PACIFICARE APPOINTS SENIOR VICE PRESIDENT FOR HEALTH 
SERVICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Dr. Sam Ho has been appointed senior vice president for health services at 
PacifiCare of California in Cypress. He is responsible for statewide and 
Western region health improvement strategies. Before joining PacifiCare, Ho was 
senior vice president and medical director for Health Net. He has also served 
as deputy director of health for community public health programs with the 
Department of Public Health in San Francisco and as a medical director for 
Maxicare and HealthAmerica. PacifiCare of California, a managed care 
organization, is a subsidiary of PacifiCare Health Systems. 
</P>
<P>
 * Don Daley Jr. has been elected chairman of the Western Growers Assn. board 
of directors for the 1995 term. He is managing partner of D. L. Daley 
Enterprises in San Diego. Western Growers, based in Irvine, is an agricultural 
trade association whose members grow, pack and ship fresh vegetables, fruit and 
nuts. 
</P>
<P>
 * Kirk A. Waldron has been appointed chief financial officer of Cybernetics 
Products Inc., a Santa Ana manufacturer of drills and routers for electronic 
circuit boards and advanced camera systems. Waldron had been interim chief 
financial officer following the resignation of Dean Trojan in August. Before 
that, he was corporate controller. Prior to joining Cybernetics in March, 
Waldron was controller of Acme Holdings Inc. Waldron has also held senior 
accounting positions with Ernst & Young LLP in Los Angeles, and with Winchell's 
Donut House Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 * Deryl Finney has been appointed director of marketing communications for 
General Automation Inc., an Anaheim computer company. He was previously senior 
director of marketing communications for AST Research Inc. for six years. 
Before that, Finney was director of public relations and advertising for 
CalComp Inc. for more than six years. 
</P>
<P>
 * Bob L. Corey has been named executive vice president of MTI Technology 
Corp., an Anaheim computer products company. He will also continue as the 
company's chief financial officer, a post he has held since joining the company 
last year. Before that, Corey was senior vice president and chief financial 
officer of Emulex Corp. He also held vice president and controller positions at 
Ashton Tate Corp. and Western Digital. 
</P>
<P>
 * Elberta Segraves has been appointed catering sales manager at the Westin 
South Coast Plaza hotel in Costa Mesa. She was previously director of catering 
at the Travelodge Resorts & Marina in Long Beach and was also director of 
catering at UC Irvine's University Club. 
</P>
</TEXT>
