<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: BABY PICTURE CONTRACTS PROVIDE BOOST FOR FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Styles on Video, a Chatsworth-based company that designs and sells imaging 
systems, said it has secured new contracts that could add as much as $2 million 
to the company's 1995 revenues. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said it has signed contracts with 40 hospitals in China and Hong 
Kong to supply digital cameras used in delivery rooms to take pictures of 
newborn babies. The company is responsible for arranging printing of the 
pictures and delivering them to the infants' parents within 24 hours. 
</P>
<P>
 Chief Executive Guy DeVreese said the company has signed similar contracts 
with 10 hospitals in the United States, and expects to sign 20 new contracts a 
month with U. S. hospitals throughout 1995. 
</P>
