<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOW TURNOUT MARS UKRAINE ELECTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Weekend parliamentary by-elections in Ukraine filled just nine of 56 vacant 
seats as voters stayed away in droves, election officials said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 They said a second round will be held in two weeks for four seats where 
turnout was more than 50% Sunday, but no candidate won an overall majority. 
Elections for the remaining 43 seats will be put off indefinitely. 
</P>
<P>
 This was the third round of parliamentary voting since March in addition to 
two rounds of presidential elections. Most Ukrainians, buffeted by post-Soviet 
economic hardships, have simply lost interest in turning out to vote. 
</P>
