<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; ILLINOIS; ROSTENKOWSKI SAYS HE'S SEEKING A JOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dan Rostenkowski, the once-powerful congressman swept out of office in Nov. 8 
elections, told the Chicago Sun-Times he has more than $500,000 in unpaid legal 
bills and is looking for work.Rostenkowski, 66, said in the interview that he 
has $230,000 in unpaid legal bills for staff members and $300,000 to $400,000 
in outstanding bills for his own legal battle against a 17-count federal 
indictment. Rostenkowski has already exhausted a $1-million campaign fund and a 
$1-million legal defense fund. The Chicago lawmaker said he was hoping to 
obtain consultant fees at corporations and was considering academic 
lectureships. 
</P>
