<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Courtney Pugmire 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza, Senior 
</P>
<P>
 Cross-country 
</P>
<P>
 Pugmire, who won the Division II 800- and 1,600-meter races at the Southern 
Section track and field championships last spring, added another title 
Saturday, winning the Division I race at the section cross-country 
championships. Pugmire ran the three-mile course at Mt.San Antonio College in 
17 minutes 45 seconds, more than a minute faster than she ran last season. 
"She's such a competitor that it doesn't matter what the distance is; she is 
going to try to win the race," Esperanza Coach Rich Medellin said. 
</P>
<P>
 Tennis 
</P>
<P>
 Michelle Weisz 
</P>
<P>
 * El Dorado, sophomore. Won her singles sets, 6-2, 6-0, 6-1, as the Golden 
Hawks beat top-seeded Hemet, 9-9 (82-75 in games) in the Division III playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 Alissa Scott 
</P>
<P>
 Nina Vaughan 
</P>
<P>
 Megan Wachtler 
</P>
<P>
 * Corona del Mar. Each won eight of nine singles sets to lead the Sea Kings to 
three Division I playoff victories and help them advance to the championship 
match. 
</P>
<P>
 Volleyball 
</P>
<P>
 Misty May 
</P>
<P>
 * Newport Harbor, senior. Averaged 29 kills and 12.5 digs in the Sailors' 
victories over Edison and Manhattan Beach Mira Costa in the Division I 
semifinals and final. 
</P>
<P>
 Courtney Owens 
</P>
<P>
 * Calvary Chapel, senior. Had 20 kills in the Eagles' three-game sweep of 
Santa Ynez in the Division IV championship match. 
</P>
