<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thad Buzolich 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar, Senior 
</P>
<P>
 Water polo/Two-meter man 
</P>
<P>
 Because the Sea Kings have so many outstanding players, Buzolich doesn't 
receive too many accolades, but Coach John Vargas is appreciative. "I think 
he's really a selfless player," Vargas said."He sits back and does all the 
little things and when we need him, he steps up and takes a big role 
offensively." Buzolich did most of his work on defense Saturday, holding 
Foothill's two-meter men to only one goal between them in Corona del Mar's 6-4 
victory in the Division I semifinal. Buzolich also scored a goal to give the 
Sea Kings a 5-2 lead. He scored three goals in a 16-7 victory over Trabuco 
Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Cross-country 
</P>
<P>
 Adalberto Sanchez 
</P>
<P>
 * Capistrano Valley, senior. Finished second in the Division I race, running 
three miles in 14 minutes 55 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
 Football 
</P>
<P>
 Jamie Hanaway 
</P>
<P>
 * El Toro, junior. Rushed for 154 yards, including a 21-yard touchdown that 
was the difference in the Chargers' 35-33 upset of second-seeded Savanna in the 
Division V playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 Sean McMahon 
</P>
<P>
 * Villa Park, senior. Completed 10 of 14 passes for 219 yards and four 
touchdowns in a 43-21 victory over Corona del Mar in a Division V playoff game. 
</P>
<P>
 Water polo 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Stanley 
</P>
<P>
 * Esperanza, senior. Scored eight goals in a 15-9 victory over University and 
five in a 9-8 victory over Tustin as the Aztecs advanced to the Division II 
championship game. 
</P>
